ex:BI0401 a skos:Concept ;
    skos:prefLabel "Insect Pest Infestations"@en ;
    skos:definition "An insect pest infestation is a recently detected insect pest population, including an incursion, or a sudden significant increase of an established insect in an area leading to damage to plants in production fields, forests or natural habitats and causing substantial damage to productivity, biodiversity or natural resources (adapted from IPPC Secretariat, 2024)."@en ;
