ex:BI0224 a skos:Concept ;
    skos:prefLabel "Mpox"@en ;
    skos:definition "Mpox, previously known as monkeypox, is a viral illness caused by the monkeypox virus, a species of the genus Orthopoxvirus. There are two distinct clades of the virus: clade I (with subclades Ia and Ib) and clade II (with subclades IIa and IIb). Mpox can be fatal in some cases (adapted from WHO, 2024)."@en ;
