    skos:definition "Crimean-Congo haemorrhagic fever (CCHF) is a tick-borne viral infection caused by the CCHF virus. It causes severe viral haemorrhagic fever outbreaks and epidemics. CCHF outbreaks have a case fatality rate of 10-40% (WHO, 2025)."@en ;
