ex:GH0310 a skos:Concept ;
    skos:prefLabel "Shrink-Swell Subsidence"@en ;
    skos:definition "Subsidence is a lowering or collapse of the ground, caused by various factors, including groundwater lowering, sub-surface mining or tunnelling, consolidation, sinkholes, or changes in moisture content in expansive soils. Shrink-swell is the term applied to the behaviour of expansive soils. These are a group of soils that exhibit volumetric change in response to changes in moisture content, such that they shrink in response to desiccation and swell by hydration, resulting in ground subsidence and ground heave respectively (BGS, 2020)."@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Shrink-swell subsidence"@da ;
    skos:prefLabel "Krimp-zwel subsidence"@nl ;
    skos:prefLabel "Shrink-Swell Subsidence"@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "laskuminen kutistumis‑ ja laajenemisen seurauksena"@fi ;
    skos:prefLabel "Affaissement par retrait-gonflement"@fr ;
    skos:prefLabel "Κατακρήμνιση συρρίκνωσης-διόγκωσης"@el ;
    skos:prefLabel "szűkítési‑ és kitágulási süllyedés"@hu ;
    skos:prefLabel "Subsidenza da ritiro-gonfiamento"@it ;
    skos:prefLabel "Shrink-swell subsidence"@lv ;
    skos:prefLabel "Susitraukimo-plečiamojo subsidavimas"@lt ;
    skos:prefLabel "Shrink-swell subsiding"@mt ;
