ex:MH0503 a skos:Concept ;
    skos:prefLabel "Dzud"@en ;
    skos:definition "A dzud (a Mongolian term that describes ‘severe winter conditions’’, sometimes spelled zud) is a cold-season disaster in which anomalous climatic (i.e., heavy snow and severe cold) and/or land-surface (snow/ ice cover and lack of pasture) conditions lead to reduced accessibility and/or availability of forage/pastures, and ultimately to high livestock mortality during winter–spring (Natsagdorj & Dulamsuren, 2001)."@en ;
