ex:BI0311 a skos:Concept ;
    skos:prefLabel "Rift Valley Fever"@en ;
    skos:definition "Rift Valley fever (RVF) is an acute haemorrhagic viral disease, affecting small and large ruminants and camels. RVF virus is a member of thePhlebovirusgenus. The disease causes high mortality, especially in newborns and mass abortions in pregnant animals. Humans become infected from contact with tissues/blood of infected animals including abortive material and through mosquito bites. Disease in humans presents as influenza-like illness, haemorrhagic fever, encephalitis and occasionally death (adapted from FAO, 2003; WHO, 2018; OIE 2020)."@en ;
